title: New York Mocha Morning
Description: Free co-working and networking with like-minded local women in business.Our Mocha Mornings are perfect for women who want a natter and settle in for a morning of co-working. If you work from home or are a successful career woman who just needs to escape the office, then our Mocha Mornings are perfect for you.All welcome, there are no fees or charges but pre-booking is essential. You will be welcomed by the Mocha Morning leader. If you would like to be introduced to anyone in particular or a feeling a little shy let your leader know, she is there to support you in any way possible.We look forward to meeting you at a Mocha Morning, if you don't find one near to you why not start your own . We offer full support and training.

title: New York Women's Business Lunch
Description: We are delighted to bring dynamic business networking to your area allowing you to connect with other businesswomen in your local community.Join us from 11:30 for our Business Lunch where we enjoy a lovely meal, an inspiring business talk and quality networking with other like-minded executives and entrepreneurs....................................................Program:11:30 Coffee & networking12:00 Introductions12:25 Member Spotlight12:30 Lunch13:00 Talk13:30 Wonderbra session14:00 End...................................................About Women's Business Club:Connecting, supporting and empowering Business Women.Join us for our Meetups and Mastermind Boardrooms across the globe....................................................Membership Info:We are a membership club and our lunches offer professional exclusivity, non-members may visit twice before deciding whether to join us. Find out more here ....................................................FAQs:Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?No we have your booking on our systemWhat is the refund policy?We can't offer refunds but you are welcome to send someone else in your place.

title: Chat with New York Times Best-selling Author AJ Jacobs
Description: A.J. Jacobs is an author, journalist, lecturer and human guinea pig. He has written multiple New York Times bestsellers that combine memoir, science, humor and a dash of self-help. During our conversation today, AJ shares a bit about his 2008 best-seller "The Year of Living Biblically" and shares some tips for aspiring writers. We even talk about some of his upcoming work too.Learn more about him at http://AJJacobs.com #AJJacobs #Religion #TheYearOfLivingBiblically
